Man: "What on earth is it?"
Rogers: "It's a Geiger counter used to locate radioactive minerals, such as uranium.
When you set up these earphones, you can even hear the effects of the atoms that the radioactivity emits in the minerals.
Evans: "Good, it's cracking about!"
"Hans" Geiger died in 1945, just a few days before his 63rd birthday.
But the invention that bears his name lives on.
